$ sysdm.cpl

*System Applet for the → Windows/control-panel[Control Panel]*

gh|Windows-Pics|/Windows/System32/sysdm.cpl/root.png||

The tab number can be specified when opening the panel from the command line like so (which goes to the third tab, that is *Advanced*):
code {
control sysdm.cpl,,3
code }

{ Opening the System Properties panel

  { Command line
    On the command line (→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`], → Windows/PowerShell), it can be started via → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/control_exe[`control.exe`] like so
code {
control sysdm.cpl
code }

  }
  { GUI

    When using the GUI only, this control panel can be opened with → Windows/control-panel[Control panel] -> → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/systemcpl_dll[System] -> *Change Settings*.

  }

}

{ Tabs

  This control panel has five tabs:
  table { ll
    Computer Name ☰
    Hardware ☰
    → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl/Advanced[Advanced] ☰ 
    → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl/System-Protection[System Protection] ☰ Change *system restore* settings
    Remote ☰
  table }

}
